![The relationship between relative speech rate and silent pause 
on "um" usage.](index_files/figure-typst/fig-rate-1.svg){#fig-rate}
:::
:::


@wieling2016 and @fruehwald2016 also found that there appears to be a language change in progress, with speakers shifting towards higher "um" usage.
As with most language changes in progress, women are in the lead.
@fig-gender plots these relationships in the data.


::: {.cell}

