# From model to meaning

## Getting predictions

We can get the probability of "um" the model assigns to each token with `marginaleffects::predictions()`.
Without passing any other arguments, it will give us back predictions for the original data.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
predictions(
  um_model
) ->
 all_pred
```
:::



::: {#tbl-pred .cell tbl-cap='Sampled rows from the item level predictions.
'}

```{.r .cell-code  code-fold="true" code-summary="Table code"}
all_pred|>
 slice_sample(
   by = label,
   n = 3
 ) |>
 tt() |>
 tt_style(
   fontsize = 0.6
 )
```

